  'The P5+1 imposed the most comprehensive financial sanctions ever applied to Iran, culminating in SWIFT disconnection in March 2012. GDP contracted 8.5%, oil exports fell 55%, and inflation exceeded 45%. Iran negotiated the JCPOA in July 2015 — the most successful sanctions case of the modern era, though the deal later collapsed after US withdrawal in 2018. Key lesson: SWIFT exclusion plus secondary sanctions on third-country banks is the most powerful financial toolkit available.'
),

