  0.45, 1, 152,
  ARRAY['August 1991: Iraq formally accepts UN resolution terms for WMD elimination; sanctions continue due to Iraqi obstruction of UNSCOM inspectors','December 1996: Oil-for-Food Program begins, allowing limited oil exports ($2 billion every 6 months) for humanitarian purposes — substantially alleviating civilian suffering but also creating a massive corruption vehicle','December 1998: Operation Desert Fox — US/UK air campaign after Iraq expels UNSCOM inspectors; inspections suspended, sanctions maintained without effective verification mechanism'],
  'Sanctions lifted May 22, 2003 following US-led invasion that toppled Saddam Hussein''s government. WMD programs were not found. Retrospective analysis concluded Iraq had terminated most WMD programs by the late 1990s under sanctions pressure, but this was not verifiable due to Iraqi obstruction.',
