  'The most comprehensive UN sanctions regime prior to the 2022 Russia package. GDP fell 75%, oil exports dropped 95%. The Oil-for-Food Program (1996-2003) was corrupted by $1.7 billion in kickbacks, illustrating the structural tension between humanitarian exceptions and regime evasion. Sanctions destroyed Iraq''s WMD programs but the success was opaque, contributing to the 2003 intelligence failure. The humanitarian catastrophe (hundreds of thousands of excess child deaths per UNICEF) catalyzed the shift to "smart sanctions" doctrine after 2003.'
),

