  '{"scenarios": [{"label": "compliance", "probability": 0.25}, {"label": "partial_compliance", "probability": 0.35}, {"label": "status_quo", "probability": 0.30}, {"label": "negotiation", "probability": 0.10}], "gdp_impact_pct": -33}',
  0.75, 24, 84,
  ARRAY['1992: UN imposes multilateral flight ban and arms embargo — the addition of UN multilateral pressure significantly increases Libya''s isolation beyond what US unilateral sanctions achieved','1999: Following Nelson Mandela and Kofi Annan mediation, Gaddafi agrees to hand over Lockerbie suspects for trial in the Netherlands under Scottish law — UN sanctions immediately suspended','2003: Libya formally accepts responsibility for Lockerbie, agrees to pay $2.7 billion compensation, and announces voluntary WMD program termination — all remaining sanctions lifted'],
  'UN sanctions suspended April 1999 when suspects transferred for trial. US sanctions progressively lifted 2003-2004 after Libya accepted Lockerbie responsibility, paid compensation, and voluntarily abandoned WMD programs. Often cited as a successful case of coercive diplomacy.',
